                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2613</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-14T13:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cipher telegram of June 12, 6 p.m. received last night. All papers today
                    publish complete denial officially given out by Foreign Office of <hi
                        rend="italic">Asahi</hi> text. I learn that papers have been cautioned to
                    refrain from further adverse comment on the American note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
